NAME
     wall - Writes to all users

SYNOPSIS
     wall

DESCRIPTION
     The wall command reads its standard input until an end-of-
     file marker.  It then sends the message to all currently
     logged in users preceded by the following introduction:

          Broadcast Message from ...

     It is used to warn all users, typically prior to shutting
     down the system.

     The sender must be the super-user.

FILES
     /dev/tty*

SEE ALSO
     mesg(1), write(1).

DIAGNOSTICS
     When an open on a user's tty file fails, the program sends
     the message Cannot send to ...


